Lemarc’s API Firewall 🛡️

A Python-based command-line project that simulates a simple firewall API. Built to practice Flask, networking, and packet filtering while logging user traffic.

What It Does

Runs a Flask API to receive network packets (5-tuple: src_ip, dest_ip, src_port, dest_port, protocol)

Filters traffic using simple rules:

Blocks certain source IPs

Blocks restricted destination ports

Allows only TCP packets

Logs all user-submitted packets to user_packets.txt with decision and reason

Supports predefined test packets and interactive user packets

Includes a master script to run tests and user packets sequentially

Firewall Rule Table ⚡
Rule #	Condition	Action	Reason
1	src_ip in blocked_ips	Block	Source IP blocked
2	protocol != TCP	Block	Only TCP allowed
3	dest_port == 22	Block	Destination Port prohibited
4	Anything else	Allow	N/A
Technologies Used 🖥️

Python 3

Flask for the API server

Requests for sending test/user packets

Built-in modules: logging, json, subprocess, sys

Example Usage ⚡

Start the firewall:

python firewall.py

Send test packets:

python test_packets.py

Send your own packets:

python user_packet.py

Optional: run all scripts automatically:

python master_script.py

Example firewall response:

{"status": "blocked", "reason": "Source IP is blocked"}

Logged entry in user_packets.txt:

src_ip: 192.168.1.10, dest_ip: 10.0.0.1, src_port: 4000, dest_port: 22, protocol: TCP, status: blocked, reason: Destination Port prohibited
